race.comment: COWARRIE (1) was beaten a nose at Seymour improving again and then tacked longer at Geelong but lacked finishing dash. Suited back to a middle distance at country level and maps for the run of the race. Looks a great chance to break through. JUSTIFIED AT LAST (6) is better than the formline suggests. Got to within 3.5L stepping up to this trip at Ballarat and that effort would see her in the money. DEEP STREAM (2) worked home well to grab third at long odds at Kilmore over 2000m. Finally draws a low gate and is on a quick back-up. Likely to feature. JAPPALOUIS (4) will use the inside barrier and was better again when narrowly beaten at Gunbower over 1800m This is tougher but he is sure to be around the mark. HARD GRUNT (3) is going well enough to consider.
